Finding aid for Roman S. Gribbs mayoral records


Finding aid created by: Finding aid prepared by Justin Lee Tyler
Date: Sept. 29, 2009

Revision history:

Title: Roman S. Gribbs mayoral records
Dates: 1952-1973
Quantity: 517.5 Linear feet(479 boxes, 4 volumes)
Language:
Language of Materials In English.
Repository: Detroit Public Library. Burton Historical Collection.

Biographical/Historical note

Sergeant, U.S. Army (1946-1948); Wayne County Prosecutor's Office, Wayne County Sheriff; Mayor of Detroit (1970-1973); Wayne County 3rd Judicial Circuit Judge (1974-1983); Justice of the Michigan Court of Appeals (1983-2000)

Scope and Contents note

This collection contains the official records and correspondence of the Gribbs Administration, from 1970-1973. It includes general files, subject files and miscellaneous files kept by his office. Materials are arranged alphabetically within the sections.

Arrangement

Series; I. 1970 (boxes 1-91C). II. 1971 (Boxes 94-210). III. 1972 (Boxes 210-354). IV. 1973 (Boxes 354-478); Each series organized into subseries: A. General files B. Subject files C. Miscellaneous files.

Restrictions

Restrictions on Access: This collection is open for research use as of Jul. 22, 2008.
